1
00:00:57,807 --> 00:01:01,394
Mom! Duk-mi is scribbling
on the ground again.

2
00:01:03,146 --> 00:01:05,482
I wasn't scribbling. I was drawing.

3
00:01:05,648 --> 00:01:07,400
To me, they look like scribbles.

4
00:01:07,484 --> 00:01:09,444
I'm just stating what I see.

5
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:11,571
Hey!

6
00:01:13,323 --> 00:01:14,449
Mom.

7
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:17,619
Duk-mi. I told you not to hit Eun-gi.

8
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:35,929
I told you you'd get in trouble
if you scribbled again.

9
00:01:36,012 --> 00:01:37,764
I told you, they're not scribbles.

10
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:40,058
Duk-mi. What are you going to become--

11
00:01:40,141 --> 00:01:42,060
What are you going to become
when you grow up?

12
00:01:42,977 --> 00:01:44,312
An artist that draws paintings.

13
00:01:44,646 --> 00:01:47,190
I'm going to hang up my paintings
in a huge gallery.

14
00:01:52,028 --> 00:01:54,280
Hey, stop that!

15
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:55,657
-Hey.
-Stop.

16
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:57,700
-Hey!
-I said, stop.

17
00:02:00,537 --> 00:02:01,913
Stop it!

18
00:03:01,681 --> 00:03:02,974
Did you have sweet dreams?

19
00:03:04,392 --> 00:03:06,144
They were sweet
because they were my memories.

20
00:03:08,897 --> 00:03:11,024
However, they were a bit sad too.

21
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,903
I played with you, Eun-gi,

22
00:03:15,862 --> 00:03:17,614
and Duk-su.

23
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:30,710
What were you doing up?

24
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:35,298
I was drawing.

25
00:03:36,716 --> 00:03:38,051
A drawing of you sleeping.

26
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:40,762
Do I look pretty in it?

27
00:03:43,181 --> 00:03:45,975
You're a woman that is out of this world,

28
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:48,895
so it's hard to express your beauty
through a drawing.

29
00:03:55,777 --> 00:03:56,903
In my dream,

30
00:03:57,737 --> 00:03:59,739
I drew with you.

31
00:04:01,032 --> 00:04:03,618
We used chalk
and drew a lot of things, here and there.

32
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:08,498
But Eun-gi said I was scribbling,
and said he'd tell Mom.

33
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:10,083
So I told him that

34
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:12,001
I'll become an artist later

35
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:14,462
and that my paintings would be
hung up in a gallery.

36
00:04:16,047 --> 00:04:16,881
Although

37
00:04:17,715 --> 00:04:19,384
I failed to become an artist,

38
00:04:19,801 --> 00:04:22,011
at least I became a person
who hangs up paintings at a gallery.

39
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:30,770
Nowadays, we don't

40
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:35,358
go to an exhibition and see
a piece of art directly.

41
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:37,902
What we see

42
00:04:38,444 --> 00:04:41,322
is a concept of what a curator
perceives as art.

43
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:42,490
Simply put,

44
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:47,203
a true artist is not the maker,
but the curator.

45
00:04:47,996 --> 00:04:49,497
Everything depends on
the curator's choice.

46
00:04:50,039 --> 00:04:51,332
Slavoj Zizek?

47
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:54,961
I totally agree with him.

48
00:04:55,628 --> 00:04:57,171
A curator is an artist, too.

49
00:04:58,631 --> 00:05:00,633
I can even draw again.

50
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:02,802
Thanks to you, Curator Sung Duk-mi.

51
00:05:04,637 --> 00:05:07,015
The exhibition room is my canvas.

52
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:11,894
However...

53
00:05:13,688 --> 00:05:14,981
Right now,

54
00:05:16,065 --> 00:05:18,693
your face seems like my canvas.

55
00:05:21,612 --> 00:05:23,156
Can I draw on it?

56
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:26,075
With what?

57
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:32,790
I'm suddenly feeling very creative.

58
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:35,418
How shall I draw on it?

59
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:38,212
Shall I begin?

60
00:05:45,303 --> 00:05:47,930
All right, shall we begin drawing
on our canvas?

61
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,390
What? Canvas?

62
00:05:50,141 --> 00:05:52,435
Let's go see Mr. No's collection first.

63
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:54,270
-Yes!
-Okay.

64
00:06:03,071 --> 00:06:05,198
I HOPE I BECOME A PART OF YOUR DREAM

65
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:06,824
-Did you check everything?
-Yes.

66
00:06:06,908 --> 00:06:08,117
Okay.

67
00:06:08,826 --> 00:06:10,912
Always leave it on channel number two.

68
00:06:10,995 --> 00:06:12,330
Make sure you keep it that way.

69
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:14,707
Okay, let's take a look
at the microphones.

70
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:16,584
Always check if it works properly.

71
00:06:18,336 --> 00:06:19,212
It's working.

72
00:06:19,295 --> 00:06:20,505
Do, mi, sol

73
00:06:20,588 --> 00:06:22,840
Welcome to the fifth-anniversary
exhibition of Cheum Museum.

74
00:06:22,924 --> 00:06:25,176
-Will this do?
-Move it a little bit to the right.

75
00:06:25,259 --> 00:06:26,636
Okay. Is this okay?

76
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:28,971
It's crooked. The right side
needs to come down a little more.

77
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:32,225
-Hyo-jin, please hurry.
-Okay, I'm done.

78
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:33,684
Okay, there we go.

79
00:06:35,561 --> 00:06:36,771
-Nice.
-It looks great.

80
00:06:36,854 --> 00:06:38,773
-You hung it nicely.
-I know.

81
00:07:02,004 --> 00:07:04,674
CHEUM'S FIFTH-ANNIVERSARY EXHIBITION
GALLERY LAYOUT

82
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:14,809
-Let's turn on the projector.
-Okay.

83
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:17,812
-You've checked the focus, right?
-Yes.

84
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:20,606
If the lighting's dark,
it'll be brighter, right?

85
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:21,774
Yes.

86
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:35,163
"The Room, The Life," Cheum Museum's
fifth-anniversary exhibition.

87
00:07:35,246 --> 00:07:36,789
We're finally holding the exhibition.

88
00:07:37,206 --> 00:07:39,959
Hyo-jin, this is your first exhibition.
How do you feel?

89
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,170
I'm excited.

90
00:07:42,336 --> 00:07:45,047
It feels as if I'm getting to meet
someone from my imagination.

91
00:07:45,173 --> 00:07:48,426
It was really hard work,
but I'm still really excited.

92
00:07:50,303 --> 00:07:52,263
Are you sure it's not because
you get to meet Mr. Cha?

93
00:07:52,513 --> 00:07:53,681
You caught me.

94
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:57,643
By the way, Director Gold.

95
00:07:57,852 --> 00:07:59,979
How did you come up
with the title of the exhibition?

96
00:08:01,689 --> 00:08:03,357
I came up with it
after I saw someone's room.

97
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:05,735
How did that room look?

98
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:08,321
The room was filled

99
00:08:08,863 --> 00:08:11,282
with cheerful, fun, and happy things.

100
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:23,794
Fill your room with the things you love

101
00:08:24,795 --> 00:08:27,590
so you can live a happier life.

102
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:34,180
We're the first ones here.

103
00:08:34,263 --> 00:08:35,348
We're the first in line.

104
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:38,226
I can't wait for the museum to open.

105
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:40,937
What do you think will be there?
Photos of Si-an?

106
00:08:43,272 --> 00:08:45,233
Si-an, can you please face the front?

107
00:08:45,483 --> 00:08:46,901
-Great.
-Please look over here.

108
00:08:46,984 --> 00:08:48,486
-Thank you.
-Please look here, too.

109
00:08:48,569 --> 00:08:49,695
-Great.
-Over here.

110
00:08:49,779 --> 00:08:51,489
-How do you feel?
-Can you wave your hand for us?

111
00:08:51,572 --> 00:08:52,740
Okay, great.

112
00:08:52,823 --> 00:08:54,825
-Nice.
-Please look over here.

113
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:57,787
-Over here.
-Okay, great.

114
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:59,038
You're doing great.

115
00:08:59,121 --> 00:09:00,998
-Please stand by the wall.
-Okay.

116
00:09:01,874 --> 00:09:03,709
Okay, great.

117
00:09:06,045 --> 00:09:07,255
Hyo-jin.

118
00:09:08,297 --> 00:09:10,299
Is that sculpture over there

119
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,552
part of the exhibition?

120
00:09:12,635 --> 00:09:14,887
Si-an really looks
like a sculpture, doesn't he?

121
00:09:15,471 --> 00:09:17,306
He's so good-looking.

122
00:09:17,723 --> 00:09:19,642
Mr. Kim, chop-chop.

123
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:37,201
Hyo-jin.

124
00:09:37,618 --> 00:09:40,037
Didn't you design that?

125
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:46,085
-Mom.
-Yes?

126
00:09:47,003 --> 00:09:50,089
I can die right now with no regrets.

127
00:09:50,172 --> 00:09:53,634
No. Hyo-jin, you can't die.
Don't say something so horrible.

128
00:09:54,969 --> 00:09:56,846
Hyo-jin, I'm so proud of you.

129
00:10:28,127 --> 00:10:29,962
Art may be great,

130
00:10:30,421 --> 00:10:32,590
but it can't be greater
than a living human being.

131
00:10:35,009 --> 00:10:36,844
Regardless of how insignificant
I may seem,

132
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:40,264
I'm still greater than
those condescending paintings

133
00:10:40,848 --> 00:10:41,932
that are hung on that wall.

134
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:46,270
Because I'm a living being,
and I will continue to live.

135
00:10:56,822 --> 00:10:59,784
These eyes aren't the eyes
of a sad farewell

136
00:10:59,867 --> 00:11:02,203
or one's eyes waiting for death.

137
00:11:02,662 --> 00:11:04,914
He's looking at someone he loves.

138
00:11:05,122 --> 00:11:07,041
He wanted to leave this for that person.

139
00:11:07,124 --> 00:11:08,751
He was looking at this person,

140
00:11:09,085 --> 00:11:11,837
and his eyes were greeting that person.

141
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,632
"Hello, I'm here.

142
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:18,469
I'm always here looking at you like this."

143
00:11:22,807 --> 00:11:23,808
Hi.

144
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:29,105
HELLO

145
00:11:40,908 --> 00:11:42,243
Soap bubbles,

146
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:45,079
a rocking horse, a Ferris wheel,
and a pirate ship ride.

147
00:11:45,746 --> 00:11:48,666
They're all things
that children especially enjoy.

148
00:11:48,999 --> 00:11:50,960
I think I know
what the artist was thinking

149
00:11:51,043 --> 00:11:53,295
when she drew these paintings.

150
00:11:54,004 --> 00:11:55,339
We're both

151
00:11:59,593 --> 00:12:00,678
smiling.

152
00:12:05,266 --> 00:12:06,851
We look very happy.

153
00:12:21,031 --> 00:12:23,659
FILL YOUR ROOM WITH THE THINGS YOU LOVE

154
00:12:23,742 --> 00:12:26,495
SO YOU CAN LIVE A HAPPIER LIFE

155
00:13:00,154 --> 00:13:01,197
Congratulations, Mom,

156
00:13:02,072 --> 00:13:03,282
on your first exhibition.

157
00:13:03,699 --> 00:13:05,117
Thank you, Si-an.

158
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:09,830
You too, Yun-jae.

159
00:13:11,207 --> 00:13:13,083
Thank you, Ms. Lee Sol.

160
00:13:14,084 --> 00:13:16,295
Thank you for letting us exhibit
your amazing paintings.

161
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:21,592
Thank you, Ms. Sung.

162
00:13:21,675 --> 00:13:22,885
Congratulations.

163
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:33,062
Would you like me
to take a photo of you guys?

164
00:13:34,897 --> 00:13:36,106
Let's take a photo.

165
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:40,277
Duk-mi is a great photographer.

166
00:14:01,590 --> 00:14:02,967
Would you like to order?

167
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:05,094
-I want an iced--
-An iced Americano

168
00:14:05,177 --> 00:14:06,929
and a latte with condensed milk
with no espresso.

169
00:14:07,012 --> 00:14:09,348
You leave out the espresso?

170
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,350
I can't drink coffee

171
00:14:12,476 --> 00:14:13,811
because I take after someone.

172
00:14:15,062 --> 00:14:16,897
Then I'll have the same thing.

173
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:19,024
A latte with condensed milk
with no espresso.

174
00:14:19,108 --> 00:14:21,193
Mr. Cha, what would you like?

175
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:24,905
I'll have what Ms. Sung is having.
An iced Americano.

176
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:28,951
Two lattes with condensed milk
with no espresso,

177
00:14:29,034 --> 00:14:30,286
one iced Americano,

178
00:14:30,828 --> 00:14:33,747
and one exquisitely delicious
iced Americano.

179
00:14:33,831 --> 00:14:35,165
I'll bring them to you soon.

180
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:51,473
Mom, I didn't know
you couldn't drink coffee.

181
00:14:52,308 --> 00:14:55,185
Ms. Lee, I thought I was your favorite.

182
00:14:55,352 --> 00:14:57,187
-Ju-hyeok.
-Yes?

183
00:14:57,354 --> 00:14:59,440
Once a fangirl, always a fangirl.

184
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:03,444
You may be my favorite,
but Si-an is on a different level.

185
00:15:04,987 --> 00:15:07,072
She must not be very interested.

186
00:15:10,242 --> 00:15:11,660
-That's a first.
-Ms. Lee.

187
00:15:12,578 --> 00:15:13,996
Yes, Mr. Cha?

188
00:15:14,788 --> 00:15:17,416
What's this music?
I've never heard of it before.

189
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:19,376
It's nice, right?

190
00:15:19,668 --> 00:15:22,338
There's a band named Fade, and

191
00:15:22,963 --> 00:15:25,174
he's the lead singer and guitarist
of that band.

192
00:15:25,341 --> 00:15:26,759
His name is Ju-hyeok.

193
00:15:27,217 --> 00:15:29,011
They're going to make an album soon.

194
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:31,305
"Fade"?

195
00:15:32,348 --> 00:15:34,934
That's great. I'll look forward
to your album.

196
00:15:35,976 --> 00:15:38,854
When the album gets released,
I'll give it to you as a gift

197
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:41,273
in person.

198
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:43,651
Okay.

199
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:51,325
Ju-hyeok, can you please pinch me?

200
00:15:58,374 --> 00:16:05,130
CHOIKANG JUDO

201
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:16,058
-We should head inside first.
-Sure.

202
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:30,948
Hello, I'm Yun-jae's mother.

203
00:16:34,535 --> 00:16:36,370
After hearing you'd be here,

204
00:16:37,663 --> 00:16:39,373
I stayed up all night

205
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:41,834
thinking about what I should say to you.

206
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:44,128
Then I realized I have nothing to say,

207
00:16:44,962 --> 00:16:46,839
except that I'm sorry.

208
00:16:48,632 --> 00:16:50,384
Yun-jae told me everything.

209
00:16:52,094 --> 00:16:53,762
Even if it was only for a short time,

210
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:57,099
I'm grateful that you looked after him.

211
00:17:37,097 --> 00:17:40,309
SUNG DUK-SU

212
00:17:41,810 --> 00:17:43,771
So this is where you were, Duk-su.

213
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:51,278
When you were young, I once brought you,

214
00:17:51,403 --> 00:17:54,239
Eun-gi, and Duk-su here to visit.

215
00:17:55,407 --> 00:17:58,118
After seeing a monk, Duk-su couldn't

216
00:17:58,202 --> 00:18:00,120
contain his laughter.

217
00:18:00,204 --> 00:18:02,790
He kept on yelling, "It's a baldy."

218
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:07,002
You can imagine how embarrassing it was.

219
00:18:09,254 --> 00:18:11,173
That's why I brought him here

220
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:12,883
so that he could have
laughter in his life.

221
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:18,055
Then I'll be the one
who brings you laughter.

222
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:26,480
I have something for you.

223
00:18:41,245 --> 00:18:42,830
I can tell by looking at these photos

224
00:18:43,122 --> 00:18:47,042
how kind and generous you were to my son.

225
00:18:48,293 --> 00:18:50,838
He looks content in these photos.

226
00:18:51,004 --> 00:18:51,964
Fortunately,

227
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:54,091
he got along well

228
00:18:54,424 --> 00:18:56,385
with Duk-mi and Eun-gi.

229
00:18:56,510 --> 00:18:58,137
He wasn't a picky eater, either.

230
00:19:09,773 --> 00:19:11,483
HEO YUN-JAE.
I MISS MY MOM. MRS. KO, THANK YOU.

231
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:13,068
DUK-MI, EUN-GI, WE'LL PLAY AGAIN SOMETIME

232
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:14,987
After Duk-su died,

233
00:19:15,571 --> 00:19:17,948
I wasn't in the right state of mind.

234
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:21,285
When I had finally pulled myself together,

235
00:19:23,245 --> 00:19:26,790
Yun-jae had already been adopted.

236
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:31,378
You went back for him

237
00:19:33,130 --> 00:19:34,756
to the orphanage he was at.

238
00:19:36,717 --> 00:19:39,219
If only I had gotten there sooner.

239
00:19:40,804 --> 00:19:43,307
There are so many things I regret.

240
00:19:44,349 --> 00:19:47,186
You and Yun-jae...

241
00:19:48,228 --> 00:19:50,314
I'm ashamed to even be in your presence.

242
00:19:51,356 --> 00:19:54,484
I'm the one who is ashamed
to look Yun-jae in the eyes.

243
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:57,738
You were in an accident.
You didn't abandon him.

244
00:19:58,906 --> 00:20:00,282
I have another son

245
00:20:01,116 --> 00:20:02,993
by the name of Si-an.

246
00:20:03,577 --> 00:20:05,370
After I lost Yun-jae,

247
00:20:05,662 --> 00:20:07,956
a man helped me look for him.

248
00:20:09,917 --> 00:20:11,376
That was Si-an's father.

249
00:20:13,462 --> 00:20:17,382
You might wonder how one
could start a family again

250
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:22,012
after losing her son.

251
00:20:23,013 --> 00:20:26,391
That son could easily
be less understanding and resentful.

252
00:20:28,018 --> 00:20:29,686
However, Yun-jae said this.

253
00:20:30,062 --> 00:20:32,898
A widow is a wife who lost her husband.

254
00:20:33,106 --> 00:20:35,859
A widower is a husband who lost his wife.

255
00:20:36,276 --> 00:20:38,195
An orphan is what you call a child

256
00:20:38,987 --> 00:20:40,280
who lost his parents.

257
00:20:41,406 --> 00:20:43,367
However, he read somewhere

258
00:20:45,535 --> 00:20:47,162
that the pain is so great

259
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:50,332
for parents who lost their children

260
