00:41:01,834 --> 00:41:03,002
Bow.

523
00:41:04,295 --> 00:41:06,046
Geon-u told me that
he's not in his best condition.

524
00:41:06,130 --> 00:41:07,590
I see. But he looks fine to me.

525
00:41:07,673 --> 00:41:11,552
First, we'll start with the back fall.

526
00:41:12,178 --> 00:41:14,180
In three, two, one.

527
00:41:15,598 --> 00:41:16,807
Okay, great.

528
00:41:16,891 --> 00:41:18,100
-Hurry up and film this.
-Okay.

529
00:41:19,727 --> 00:41:22,730
Okay, great.
Next, let's see you do a front fall.

530
00:41:22,897 --> 00:41:25,983
One, two, three. Go.

531
00:41:26,609 --> 00:41:27,985
Great. Now, get back up.

532
00:41:29,528 --> 00:41:33,032
Next, let's see you do a side fall.
One, two, three. Go.

533
00:41:36,118 --> 00:41:37,411
He's so cute.

534
00:41:38,120 --> 00:41:39,330
Get back up.

535
00:41:39,455 --> 00:41:40,623
Isn't he so cute?

536
00:41:41,207 --> 00:41:43,375
What are you doing?
Why are you filming me?

537
00:41:43,459 --> 00:41:45,794
I'm filming what looks cute to me.

538
00:41:46,587 --> 00:41:49,548
My gosh, hurry up and film Geon-u.
Come on.

539
00:41:51,175 --> 00:41:54,053
Now, it's Kang Geon-u's turn.
Please come forward.

540
00:41:55,930 --> 00:41:57,056
What's my name?

541
00:41:57,181 --> 00:41:59,183
Nam Eun-gi!

542
00:42:01,018 --> 00:42:02,686
Mr. Nam Eun-gi!

543
00:42:04,230 --> 00:42:05,397
That's right.

544
00:42:06,774 --> 00:42:08,150
Here's your yellow belt.

545
00:42:17,034 --> 00:42:18,619
Go back to your place. Go on.

546
00:42:20,204 --> 00:42:21,205
Okay, next.

547
00:42:21,288 --> 00:42:23,332
-Yu-seop.
-Yes, Ms. Sung?

548
00:42:23,415 --> 00:42:25,125
Did you complete the insurance contract

549
00:42:25,209 --> 00:42:26,877
for Mr. Ahn's Mono Art Gallery exhibition?

550
00:42:26,961 --> 00:42:29,171
Yes, you just need to fix
the date of shipment.

551
00:42:57,825 --> 00:42:59,034
Thank you.

552
00:42:59,410 --> 00:43:02,538
Does that mean Ms. Sung needs
to go to the States?

553
00:43:02,621 --> 00:43:03,747
Duk-mi's going to the States?

554
00:43:03,831 --> 00:43:06,709
It's not settled yet, but she got
a request from Mono Art Gallery.

555
00:43:07,167 --> 00:43:09,628
They asked if she could participate
in curating Mr. Ahn's exhibition

556
00:43:09,712 --> 00:43:11,046
since she's the one in charge.

557
00:43:11,130 --> 00:43:13,132
Either that or they asked
if she could recommend anyone.

558
00:43:13,215 --> 00:43:15,884
It's too bad they wanted someone with
at least five years of work experience.

559
00:43:16,093 --> 00:43:17,386
What a relief.

560
00:43:18,804 --> 00:43:20,848
Ms. Sung would go, wouldn't she?

561
00:43:20,931 --> 00:43:23,350
If she goes, she'll have to be there
for at least 6 to 12 months.

562
00:43:23,434 --> 00:43:25,185
There's no way she'd leave
without Director Gold.

563
00:43:25,894 --> 00:43:28,856
-You don't think she'll go, right?
-But she loves her work. She'll go, right?

564
00:43:29,315 --> 00:43:31,317
-I don't think she'll go.
-I don't think she'll go either.

565
00:43:39,033 --> 00:43:40,159
Do you want to bet 5,000 won?

566
00:43:40,242 --> 00:43:41,910
-I bet that she won't go.
-I bet that she will.

567
00:43:41,994 --> 00:43:43,495
-She won't go.
-I think she'll decide to go

568
00:43:43,579 --> 00:43:45,247
-and then change her mind.
-That's cheating.

569
00:43:47,333 --> 00:43:48,751
I bet she'll go.

570
00:43:50,628 --> 00:43:51,670
Should I stay out of it?

571
00:43:51,754 --> 00:43:53,339
-You should've done that earlier.
-Okay.

572
00:43:58,010 --> 00:43:59,219
Why aren't you telling me

573
00:43:59,553 --> 00:44:01,513
that they asked you to work
as a curator in New York?

574
00:44:05,267 --> 00:44:07,770
Did you perhaps
have anything to do with it?

575
00:44:08,729 --> 00:44:10,439
I only found out today

576
00:44:11,023 --> 00:44:14,276
that Mono Art Gallery
wants you as their curator.

577
00:44:14,860 --> 00:44:16,236
Have you given it some thought?

578
00:44:16,695 --> 00:44:17,780
Yes.

579
00:44:18,072 --> 00:44:19,365
And have you decided?

580
00:44:20,240 --> 00:44:21,367
Yes.

581
00:44:23,035 --> 00:44:24,244
So you're going.

582
00:44:24,953 --> 00:44:26,121
Yes.

583
00:44:27,081 --> 00:44:28,374
You made the right choice.

584
00:44:29,083 --> 00:44:30,793
This is a great opportunity for you.

585
00:44:32,127 --> 00:44:35,964
Does that mean we'll be
in a long-distance relationship now?

586
00:44:37,341 --> 00:44:38,634
It's kind of romantic.

587
00:44:39,134 --> 00:44:41,136
But I'm going to go with you.

588
00:44:44,431 --> 00:44:47,226
Come with me, Artist Ryan Gold.

589
00:44:49,103 --> 00:44:51,605
I analyzed your artwork
before your retirement

590
00:44:51,688 --> 00:44:54,066
as well as the current art trend

591
00:44:54,149 --> 00:44:55,818
in New York.

592
00:44:56,193 --> 00:44:58,112
Your artwork

593
00:44:58,195 --> 00:45:00,864
is good enough to make a comeback with.

594
00:45:01,740 --> 00:45:04,827
Actually, people might be more
shocked than they were at your debut.

595
00:45:07,996 --> 00:45:09,665
I'm asking you to trust me.

596
00:45:10,165 --> 00:45:13,043
Trust my instincts and taste as a curator.

597
00:45:15,295 --> 00:45:16,588
I do trust you.

598
00:45:17,214 --> 00:45:19,299
I trust you as a curator, too.

599
00:45:23,971 --> 00:45:26,932
But if I go to New York now,
I'll be a jobless man.

600
00:45:27,891 --> 00:45:30,602
-How will I manage?
-I'll pay for both of us.

601
00:45:30,936 --> 00:45:32,604
-Really?
-Yes.

602
00:45:34,815 --> 00:45:38,277
Just so you know,
I have to eat steak every day.

603
00:45:38,569 --> 00:45:40,195
Would that be manageable?

604
00:45:41,238 --> 00:45:42,698
Every day?

605
00:45:43,532 --> 00:45:44,491
Steak?

606
00:45:44,575 --> 00:45:47,953
It's fine. I hear that meat
is cheaper in the US.

607
00:45:48,245 --> 00:45:50,581
I know many tasty
but affordable restaurants in New York.

608
00:45:50,664 --> 00:45:51,582
Really?

609
00:45:54,585 --> 00:45:57,629
I always felt bad for
not letting you study abroad,

610
00:45:58,547 --> 00:46:00,632
but you're finally going.

611
00:46:01,550 --> 00:46:03,135
Take care, all right?

612
00:46:03,677 --> 00:46:05,929
-Sure.
-So with Director Gold--

613
00:46:06,013 --> 00:46:08,098
Please call me Yun-jae.

614
00:46:10,976 --> 00:46:14,229
Well, I'm relieved
that you're going with her.

615
00:46:14,771 --> 00:46:16,607
Please look after Duk-mi.

616
00:46:16,690 --> 00:46:19,109
Of course. We'll call often, too.

617
00:46:20,402 --> 00:46:22,946
Will you be saying goodbye
to his mother, too?

618
00:46:23,447 --> 00:46:25,115
Of course. We're meeting her today.

619
00:46:25,199 --> 00:46:26,825
She must be sad

620
00:46:26,909 --> 00:46:28,994
since she just got you back.

621
00:46:29,870 --> 00:46:32,080
You don't have to call us often,

622
00:46:32,164 --> 00:46:33,999
so call her more instead.

623
00:46:34,166 --> 00:46:36,793
I will call you both often.

624
00:46:40,589 --> 00:46:43,050
I'm glad that you're able to paint again.

625
00:46:44,593 --> 00:46:46,178
I owe it all to Duk-mi.

626
00:46:47,471 --> 00:46:48,889
Well, I'm grateful.

627
00:46:49,723 --> 00:46:53,685
They're both leaving,
so can't you at least stay?

628
00:46:53,769 --> 00:46:56,355
Goodness. Look who's a baby again.

629
00:46:56,438 --> 00:46:59,191
Are you heading back
to where your husband is?

630
00:47:00,442 --> 00:47:01,527
Yes.

631
00:47:01,610 --> 00:47:04,571
Both of my sons are doing so well,

632
00:47:04,655 --> 00:47:06,031
so I should do the same.

633
00:47:06,490 --> 00:47:09,368
Working as a volunteer teaching Korean
to Korean children who were adopted abroad

634
00:47:09,451 --> 00:47:11,203
was how I met Yun-jae again.

635
00:47:11,286 --> 00:47:13,622
I'm taking it as a sign
to work even harder.

636
00:47:15,832 --> 00:47:18,252
Mr. Cha seems quite upset, though.

637
00:47:18,502 --> 00:47:20,212
Actually, it's not because of us,

638
00:47:21,213 --> 00:47:23,048
-but because of a certain fan.
-A fan?

639
00:47:23,131 --> 00:47:26,885
Yes, what was her name again?
It was The Road to...

640
00:47:26,969 --> 00:47:28,762
The Road to Si-an.

641
00:47:29,471 --> 00:47:32,266
She put her fan site on hold.

642
00:47:33,016 --> 00:47:35,769
It's just a short break, so I'll...

643
00:47:37,396 --> 00:47:39,856
I'm sure she'll be back
as your fan someday.

644
00:47:45,112 --> 00:47:46,321
Cha Si-an.

645
00:47:48,073 --> 00:47:49,199
Si-an!

646
00:47:54,580 --> 00:47:57,040
Your mom, Duk-mi, and I
will be back, all right?

647
00:48:08,802 --> 00:48:10,137
I'm sure you all know by now, but--

648
00:48:10,220 --> 00:48:11,722
Can't you stay?

649
00:48:11,805 --> 00:48:13,015
We can't.

650
00:48:14,725 --> 00:48:16,560
I won't be gone for long.

651
00:48:17,102 --> 00:48:18,562
Says who?

652
00:48:21,690 --> 00:48:24,651
This isn't a permanent farewell,
so we'll keep it short.

653
00:48:25,110 --> 00:48:26,945
You all did a great job.

654
00:48:27,029 --> 00:48:28,447
Thank you.

655
00:48:28,530 --> 00:48:30,532
Once you make a comeback as an artist,

656
00:48:30,616 --> 00:48:32,701
you can hold an exhibition here.

657
00:48:32,784 --> 00:48:34,119
What's there to be upset about?

658
00:48:34,202 --> 00:48:37,789
Hyo-jin, you seem oddly excited.

659
00:48:40,083 --> 00:48:43,378
Anyway, now it's time to introduce you
to your new director.

660
00:48:45,255 --> 00:48:47,633
I'm afraid I couldn't stop this.

661
00:48:54,264 --> 00:48:58,101
I'm your new director,
Director Eom So-hye.

662
00:48:58,477 --> 00:48:59,645
Ta-da.

663
00:48:59,728 --> 00:49:01,688
It's my mom!

664
00:49:04,107 --> 00:49:05,942
You all seem thrilled.

665
00:49:10,864 --> 00:49:13,325
Duk-mi. My Duk-mi.

666
00:49:14,284 --> 00:49:16,703
How am I going to survive without you?

667
00:49:16,912 --> 00:49:18,121
I'll call you every day.

668
00:49:18,205 --> 00:49:19,790
How would that suffice

669
00:49:19,873 --> 00:49:21,958
when we spend 360 days a year together?

670
00:49:22,042 --> 00:49:24,211
She'll be back, you know, and time flies.

671
00:49:24,294 --> 00:49:27,839
You can't understand since you've spent

672
00:49:27,923 --> 00:49:29,966
time away from her
while you were training,

673
00:49:30,258 --> 00:49:31,760
but that's not the case for me.

674
00:49:31,843 --> 00:49:33,762
The only time we spent apart

675
00:49:34,054 --> 00:49:37,933
is when I was at the facility
recovering from childbirth.

676
00:49:38,016 --> 00:49:40,477
Actually, don't you remember

677
00:49:40,560 --> 00:49:43,188
when I sneaked in
disguised as your husband?

678
00:49:43,271 --> 00:49:44,147
Right.

679
00:49:46,608 --> 00:49:47,984
Director Gold,

680
00:49:48,443 --> 00:49:50,112
please be good to her.

681
00:49:50,821 --> 00:49:52,823
-I will.
-My Duk-mi

682
00:49:52,906 --> 00:49:55,075
likes handsome men the most.

683
00:49:55,158 --> 00:49:56,618
-Hey!
-She's not drunk yet.

684
00:49:56,702 --> 00:49:58,495
She likes pretty boys, too.

685
00:49:58,578 --> 00:49:59,830
-Right.
-Seon-ju.

686
00:49:59,913 --> 00:50:01,331
She goes crazy

687
00:50:01,873 --> 00:50:02,958
for cute guys.

688
00:50:03,333 --> 00:50:07,003
All right. Handsome, pretty, and cute.

689
00:50:07,087 --> 00:50:08,672
I'll try to be all those things.

690
00:50:10,090 --> 00:50:13,593
I remember you being shy
when you were young.

691
00:50:14,678 --> 00:50:15,637
Me?

692
00:50:15,721 --> 00:50:17,597
Yes, you.

693
00:50:19,933 --> 00:50:21,059
Seriously?

694
00:50:21,643 --> 00:50:24,271
Director Gold,
please coach Eun-gi on dating.

695
00:50:25,689 --> 00:50:26,732
Cheers.

696
00:50:27,524 --> 00:50:28,859
She's always been funny.

697
00:50:30,736 --> 00:50:31,945
Director Gold.

698
00:50:32,696 --> 00:50:34,072
I'm not a director anymore.

699
00:50:34,239 --> 00:50:37,200
Oh, right. Then Lion.

700
00:50:38,744 --> 00:50:41,204
It's not Lion. It's Ryan.

701
00:50:43,165 --> 00:50:44,332
You choose, then.

702
00:50:44,958 --> 00:50:47,836
Lion, Ryan, or Yun-jae.

703
00:50:48,253 --> 00:50:49,921
What should I call you?

704
00:50:51,840 --> 00:50:53,925
Will you call me by the name I pick?

705
00:50:54,009 --> 00:50:55,719
Of course, so choose one.

706
00:50:59,598 --> 00:51:01,057
If that's the case,

707
00:51:02,100 --> 00:51:04,478
I need you to listen to me closely.

708
00:51:09,691 --> 00:51:11,276
You once told me

709
00:51:13,820 --> 00:51:14,863
that my artwork

710
00:51:15,697 --> 00:51:17,407
had improved.

711
00:51:21,620 --> 00:51:23,246
I didn't know before

712
00:51:26,458 --> 00:51:29,002
that there were so many things
I wished to paint.

713
00:51:34,007 --> 00:51:35,133
The sound of breathing,

714
00:51:36,259 --> 00:51:37,636
the scent of the wind,

715
00:51:39,304 --> 00:51:40,597
the warm sun,

716
00:51:49,773 --> 00:51:50,649
and...

717
00:51:53,735 --> 00:51:55,362
the warmth of the woman I love.

718
00:52:05,580 --> 00:52:07,874
I know this might seem too sudden,

719
00:52:09,417 --> 00:52:11,002
but bear with me today.

720
00:52:12,254 --> 00:52:14,506
This just feels like the right moment.

721
00:52:16,424 --> 00:52:18,677
I'm telling you
because I don't want to wait.

722
00:52:29,646 --> 00:52:30,772
Duk-mi,

723
00:52:34,150 --> 00:52:35,986
more than anyone in this world,

724
00:52:37,737 --> 00:52:38,697
I wish

725
00:52:40,657 --> 00:52:42,909
to paint your happiness by your side.

726
00:52:49,082 --> 00:52:50,375
Will you marry me?

727
00:53:03,930 --> 00:53:05,390
Since I'm a fangirl,

728
00:53:06,766 --> 00:53:08,560
I'll answer in my language.

729
00:53:13,857 --> 00:53:15,066
Yes.

730
00:53:17,360 --> 00:53:19,404
I will be your favorite star.

731
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:26,286
Will you be

732
00:53:28,288 --> 00:53:30,123
my favorite star as well?

733
00:53:40,258 --> 00:53:41,384
Forever.

734
00:54:41,987 --> 00:54:43,863
Oh, my goodness!

735
00:54:44,072 --> 00:54:45,156
Thank you.

736
00:54:45,240 --> 00:54:46,950
Give me Cha Si-an's album.

737
00:54:47,075 --> 00:54:48,243
Here.

738
00:54:49,661 --> 00:54:50,912
-Give me a box.
-Me too.

739
00:54:50,996 --> 00:54:52,288
-I'll take a box too.
-Me too.

740
00:54:52,831 --> 00:54:54,040
I can't believe it.

741
00:54:54,124 --> 00:54:55,333
This is amazing!

742
00:54:55,709 --> 00:54:56,876
Isn't that heavy?

743
00:54:56,960 --> 00:54:58,503
INDIE MUSIC

744
00:54:58,837 --> 00:55:03,925
US, EACH OTHER'S STAR

745
00:55:07,595 --> 00:55:10,223
Geon-u, don't fight with your friends.

746
00:55:10,432 --> 00:55:12,434
If there's something you don't know,
ask your teacher.

747
00:55:13,309 --> 00:55:16,229
-Geon-u, you can do it.
-I can do it.

748
00:55:17,022 --> 00:55:18,898
I'll see you later, Mom.

749
00:55:19,024 --> 00:55:20,859
I'll see you later, Dad.

750
00:55:21,985 --> 00:55:23,194
Have fun!

751
00:55:23,528 --> 00:55:25,071
Jae-ha!

752
00:55:27,490 --> 00:55:29,242
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

753
00:55:29,451 --> 00:55:31,202
-We have free time!
-Yes!

754
00:55:49,888 --> 00:55:53,975
ONE YEAR LATER

755
00:56:13,119 --> 00:56:15,330
My husband, Mu-san!

756
00:56:22,295 --> 00:56:23,505
Mu-san!

757
00:56:26,716 --> 00:56:29,219
Mu-san. Do you know how much I missed you?

758
00:56:29,302 --> 00:56:32,055
-Sure...
-Do you really know?

759
00:56:32,180 --> 00:56:33,348
Of course.

760
00:56:33,640 --> 00:56:34,891
I missed you like mad.

761
00:56:36,976 --> 00:56:39,395
Mu-san. Why did you gain so much weight?

762
00:56:41,147 --> 00:56:42,982
Your face is so swollen.

763
00:56:43,108 --> 00:56:45,068
Did the food in there suit you well?

764
00:56:48,488 --> 00:56:49,322
Mr. Kim.

765
00:56:51,157 --> 00:56:52,325
Mu-san.

766
00:56:54,577 --> 00:56:57,080
Mu-san. You should go on a diet now.

767
00:56:57,497 --> 00:56:58,623
Here.

768
00:57:02,252 --> 00:57:04,379
Men should look handsome.
You know that, right?

769
00:57:04,462 --> 00:57:06,172
You should maintain your looks
until you're dead.

770
00:57:06,256 --> 00:57:07,090
One more time.

771
00:57:11,136 --> 00:57:12,345
You look more handsome now.

772
00:57:18,935 --> 00:57:20,937
-Ms. Yang Eun-ha.
-Yes?

773
00:57:22,313 --> 00:57:24,065
You've never made coffee before, have you?

774
00:57:25,817 --> 00:57:26,985
No.

775
00:57:31,322 --> 00:57:32,574
Watch carefully.

776
00:57:33,700 --> 00:57:34,951
Tear this...

777
00:57:36,703 --> 00:57:37,787
and pour it in.

778
00:57:37,871 --> 00:57:39,914
Is Hyo-jin making coffee?

779
00:57:40,373 --> 00:57:43,418
That is what you call
a talented individual.

780
00:57:44,043 --> 00:57:46,171
Mu-san should be here to see this.

781
00:57:50,842 --> 00:57:54,471
The reason I suddenly asked
for a meeting like this

782
00:57:54,929 --> 00:57:57,348
is because there is someone
I'd like to introduce.

783
00:57:58,475 --> 00:58:01,978
Of course, all this time, I took care of

784
00:58:02,061 --> 00:58:05,190
all the work here without any problems,

785
00:58:05,273 --> 00:58:06,608
but our workload has increased.

786
00:58:06,691 --> 00:58:08,443
It's difficult to handle on our own.

787
00:58:08,776 --> 00:58:13,823
Mu-san might be upset
since I'm so busy with work.

788
00:58:15,283 --> 00:58:17,619
So I think it's time to bring in

789
00:58:17,702 --> 00:58:19,996
our new vice-director.

790
00:58:20,497 --> 00:58:21,664
Come in.

791
00:58:22,999 --> 00:58:24,209
She's not coming in.

792
00:58:24,834 --> 00:58:26,628
Come on in!

793
00:58:37,055 --> 00:58:40,767
Hello. I'm the vice-director of
Cheum Museum, Sung Duk-mi.

794
00:58:41,726 --> 00:58:43,269
-Ms. Sung!
-Ms. Sung!

795
00:58:44,270 --> 00:58:45,688
How have you all been?

796
00:58:45,772 --> 00:58:48,191
You look just as happy
as when I came here. That's a relief.

797
00:58:48,274 --> 00:58:49,859
Come on over.

798
00:58:49,943 --> 00:58:52,070
You should all take time
to catch up, then.

799
00:58:55,949 --> 00:58:57,325
My goodness!

800
00:59:00,745 --> 00:59:02,330
I heard you became the head curator.

801
00:59:02,455 --> 00:59:03,957
Curator Sung... No,

802
00:59:04,040 --> 00:59:07,126
Vice-director Sung.
I filled in perfectly for you.

803
00:59:08,253 --> 00:59:09,921
Yu-seop, what about you?
Are you a curator now?

804
00:59:10,004 --> 00:59:13,466
Yes. And Ms. Yu and I are going out now.

805
00:59:16,052 --> 00:59:18,096
It's seriously annoying.

806
00:59:18,179 --> 00:59:20,932
Why does everyone at this museum
end up dating?

807
00:59:21,307 --> 00:59:22,850
Is Director Gold...

808
00:59:23,893 --> 00:59:26,896
I mean, is Artist Ryan Gold coming too?

809
00:59:27,355 --> 00:59:29,774
Artist Ryan Gold?

810
00:59:44,706 --> 00:59:47,292
What does that mean?

811
00:59:48,710 --> 00:59:51,254
It means our son-in-law Ryan

812
00:59:51,879 --> 00:59:53,214
has returned.

813
00:59:54,716 --> 00:59:56,050
-Impressive.
-Gosh.

814
00:59:56,134 --> 00:59:58,886
I told you to study English with me.

815
00:59:59,512 --> 01:00:00,805
Hold on.

816
01:00:02,265 --> 01:00:03,391
Mom.

817
01:00:04,726 --> 01:00:05,935
Duk-mi.

818
01:00:06,728 --> 01:00:08,229
Duk-mi! Oh, gosh.

819
01:00:08,313 --> 01:00:09,897
My gosh, come here.

820
01:00:10,148 --> 01:00:12,900
My daughter. Let me see you.

821
01:00:21,993 --> 01:00:23,244
Is today my birthday or something?

822
01:00:23,328 --> 01:00:25,622
My daughter Duk-mi has finally returned.

823
01:00:25,705 --> 01:00:27,123
We need to have a feast.

824
01:00:27,582 --> 01:00:30,001
Congratulations, Vice-director
Sung Duk-mi.

825
01:00:30,084 --> 01:00:32,128
I look forward to
your collaboration with Moment.

826
01:00:32,211 --> 01:00:34,130
I look forward to it, too.

827
01:00:36,841 --> 01:00:39,302
-Dad.
-Dad. Are you crying?

828
01:00:40,261 --> 01:00:42,472
No. Go on and eat.

829
01:00:42,555 --> 01:00:44,182
You're so silly.

830
01:00:45,058 --> 01:00:48,269
By the way, when is Ryan coming?

831
01:00:48,436 --> 01:00:51,272
Yun-jae? He's busy with exhibitions
until early next year

832
01:00:51,356 --> 01:00:52,982
so he won't be able to come soon.

833
01:00:53,066 --> 01:00:54,901
That means he has successfully
made his comeback,

834
01:00:54,984 --> 01:00:56,402
so there's no need to feel upset.

835
01:00:56,653 --> 01:00:58,154
I don't feel upset.

836
01:00:59,572 --> 01:01:01,282
I set a date for your wedding.

837
01:01:01,908 --> 01:01:03,034
Wedding?

838
01:01:04,535 --> 01:01:06,954
I think Eun-gi might hold a wedding first.

839
01:01:07,121 --> 01:01:08,581
-What?
-What?

840
01:01:09,582 --> 01:01:12,043
What?

841
01:01:12,627 --> 01:01:13,878
I'm not seeing anyone.

842
01:01:13,961 --> 01:01:16,172
You were talking with Ms. Choi
on the phone often lately.

843
01:01:16,255 --> 01:01:18,925
-That's because she just...
-Just what?

844
01:01:19,509 --> 01:01:21,219
It seems like they're quite close.

845
01:01:21,594 --> 01:01:22,845
-Right?
-Yes.

846
01:01:23,179 --> 01:01:24,931
It's not her.

847
01:01:25,890 --> 01:01:27,141
There's someone else.

848
01:01:28,059 --> 01:01:30,103
-Really? There is someone?
-I just got chills.

849
01:01:30,228 --> 01:01:32,855
You don't even know anything.
Go on and eat.

850
01:01:33,064 --> 01:01:34,816
-He must be hiding something.
-I know.

851
01:01:34,899 --> 01:01:36,984
Who is it? I know everyone that you know.

852
01:01:37,068 --> 01:01:38,236
Who is it?

853
01:01:40,947 --> 01:01:42,115
Be careful.

854
01:01:47,787 --> 01:01:48,996
You're here.

855
01:01:51,833 --> 01:01:53,918
-Welcome.
-Seon-ju.

856
01:01:55,211 --> 01:01:56,754
Is this your little baby?

857
01:01:56,838 --> 01:01:58,047
"Hello, Auntie."

858
01:01:58,131 --> 01:02:00,258
-Will you be cuter than Geon-u?
-Yes.

859
01:02:02,677 --> 01:02:04,429
I thought you didn't have plans
for a second child.

860
01:02:04,554 --> 01:02:06,097
It just happened.

861
01:02:06,639 --> 01:02:07,682
Congratulations.

862
01:02:07,765 --> 01:02:10,768
Right. Today's the day of
Si-an and Ju-hyeok's

863
01:02:10,852 --> 01:02:13,646
first performance since they released
their project album.

864
01:02:13,771 --> 01:02:15,356
Will you go with me?

865
01:02:15,773 --> 01:02:17,775
I will. Of course, I'll go.

866
01:02:19,902 --> 01:02:21,654
Are you two back to fangirling again?

867
01:02:21,904 --> 01:02:24,949
Oh, right. Don't be shocked
when you see Ju-hyeok.

868
01:02:25,158 --> 01:02:26,242
Why?

869
01:02:26,617 --> 01:02:28,035
He thinks of himself as a total hotshot.

870
01:02:28,536 --> 01:02:31,998
Hey, he can fix that anytime.
That's not what's important right now.

871
01:02:32,081 --> 01:02:33,291
Eun-gi has a girl.

872
01:02:33,583 --> 01:02:35,543
-What?
-I told you it's not true.

873
01:02:35,626 --> 01:02:37,462
Is it her? That artist?

874
01:02:37,545 --> 01:02:39,088
It's not her. It's someone else.

875
01:02:39,172 --> 01:02:40,840
-You're mistaken.
-Who is it?

876
01:02:40,923 --> 01:02:42,592
-You didn't hear anything?
-No.

877
01:02:42,675 --> 01:02:43,634
You didn't know, right?

878
01:02:43,718 --> 01:02:45,595
-What have you been doing?
-I told you it's not true.

879
01:02:45,845 --> 01:02:47,054
-What have you been up to?
-Eun-gi.

880
01:02:47,138 --> 01:02:49,015
-I was just joking.
-You're all grown up.

881
01:02:49,098 --> 01:02:50,892
-You're an adult now.
-Is it someone I know?

882
01:02:50,975 --> 01:02:52,101
-Hey.
-Who is it?

883
01:02:52,602 --> 01:02:55,354
-Nam Eun-gi's "Life of Judo"!
-"Life of Judo"!

884
01:02:57,690 --> 01:03:01,569
Today, we will learn about
the Tai Otoshi judo throw.

885
01:03:01,652 --> 01:03:02,612
Before we learn it...

886
01:03:03,571 --> 01:03:06,282
-Please subscribe to our channel.
-And press the like button.

887
01:03:06,532 --> 01:03:08,743
-We look forward to your support.
-Thank you.

888
01:03:10,828 --> 01:03:13,456
Mr. Nam, when is
the Tai Otoshi throw used?

889
01:03:13,539 --> 01:03:15,666
Well, it is used

890
01:03:15,750 --> 01:03:18,669
when you and your opponent
are grappling each other.

891
01:03:18,753 --> 01:03:20,129
When you want to do a shoulder throw,

892
01:03:20,213 --> 01:03:21,964
but when the opponent's
front leg is blocking you,

893
01:03:22,048 --> 01:03:24,050
you might hurt your tailbone
due to the opponent's knee.

894
01:03:24,133 --> 01:03:25,176
Take a look.

895
01:03:27,887 --> 01:03:29,055
It's short.

896
01:03:29,764 --> 01:03:32,683
You might not get hurt
if the opponent's leg is short...

897
01:03:36,938 --> 01:03:38,648
What are you doing?

898
01:03:39,065 --> 01:03:40,983
That really hurts.

899
01:03:41,067 --> 01:03:43,778
Man up. It's not easy
to make money, you know.

900
01:03:43,861 --> 01:03:45,363
Are you sure we can make money with this?

901
01:03:48,324 --> 01:03:52,370
Mister, you're good at eating, aren't you?

902
01:03:53,287 --> 01:03:54,288
Come here.

903
01:03:54,914 --> 01:03:56,082
-Let's do a shoulder throw.
-Why?

904
01:03:56,165 --> 01:03:58,918
-Come here.
-Eating shows are a trend lately.

905
01:03:59,710 --> 01:04:01,796
-I'll buy you food.
-Cut the nonsense.

906
01:04:02,046 --> 01:04:04,298
-Let's do an eating show.
-Let's turn off the camera.

907
01:04:05,299 --> 01:04:07,218
Help me.

908
01:04:08,219 --> 01:04:11,055
VICE-DIRECTOR, SUNG DUK-MI

909
01:04:24,318 --> 01:04:25,862
Vice-director Sung.

910
01:04:27,280 --> 01:04:28,698
It's time for the meeting.

911
01:04:29,198 --> 01:04:30,283
Okay.

912
01:05:13,326 --> 01:05:15,119
Yes, this is Sung Duk-mi.

913
01:05:15,786 --> 01:05:17,788
You don't sound pleased
to hear my voice at all.

914
01:05:18,915 --> 01:05:21,042
It hasn't even been a week
since I came here.

915
01:05:23,044 --> 01:05:25,796
I feel as if it's been about seven years.

916
01:05:25,922 --> 01:05:27,673
How are preparations
for the exhibition going?

917
01:05:27,757 --> 01:05:29,884
I just finished a meeting,
and I called because I missed you.

918
01:05:29,967 --> 01:05:32,094
How's Cheum Museum? Is everything well?

919
01:05:33,054 --> 01:05:35,056
Everything's exactly the same,
including Director Eom.

920
01:05:35,222 --> 01:05:37,141
Is that place also the same?

921
01:05:37,224 --> 01:05:38,267
What place?

922
01:05:38,351 --> 01:05:41,646
The place where we took photos
when we were faking our relationship.

923
01:05:44,899 --> 01:05:46,067
Oh, this place?

924
01:05:46,984 --> 01:05:48,861
Everything's the same here as well,

925
01:05:49,195 --> 01:05:50,613
except for one thing.

926
01:05:50,696 --> 01:05:53,032
Except for one thing? What's that?

927
01:05:54,992 --> 01:05:56,035
My Lion isn't here.

928
01:06:03,292 --> 01:06:04,877
Does this make everything the same again?

929
01:06:07,338 --> 01:06:09,465
What happened? When did you come?

930
01:06:09,548 --> 01:06:10,800
What about the exhibition?

931
01:06:11,258 --> 01:06:13,094
I came as soon as the meeting ended.

932
01:06:13,552 --> 01:06:15,262
I missed you like crazy.

933
01:06:15,680 --> 01:06:17,264
I told you that I'll go once it's over.

934
01:06:17,682 --> 01:06:19,308
You're the one who made me
become like this.

935
01:06:20,142 --> 01:06:23,187
To be honest, I was also
having a hard time without you.

936
01:06:29,068 --> 01:06:30,736
-Duk-mi.
-Yes?

937
01:06:31,237 --> 01:06:33,114
This is what a fan should do.

938
01:06:36,117 --> 01:06:37,451
You're a successful fan.

939
01:06:39,495 --> 01:06:40,830
Do you want me?

940
01:06:41,747 --> 01:06:42,790
Yes.

941
01:07:39,722 --> 01:07:40,639
Are you

942
01:07:40,806 --> 01:07:42,349
currently a fan?

943
01:07:43,267 --> 01:07:45,394
I hope you become a successful fan.

944
01:08:42,910 --> 01:08:45,079
Subtitle translation by Ju-young Park

